Page 3
S.B. NO. Sg?,
C.D. 1
1 Eight subcommittees were formed, and each subcommittee
2 convened numerous times to consider and prepare proposed
3 revisions to designated parts of the Penal Code and to related
4 statutes outside the Penal Code, for submission to the entire
5 advisory committee. The advisory committee on penal code review
6 met in plenary session nine times between November 1, 2024, and
7 October 31, 2025, and recommended statutory changes that are
8 reflected in the legislation proposed by this Act.
9 The purpose of this Act is to amend various chapters of the
10 Hawaii Penal Code, and related statutes outside the Penal Code,
11 pursuant to the recommendations of the advisory committee on
12 penal code review.
